  "datePublished": "2026-03-06",
  "description": "A ***counterargument*** is an objection to the writer's [thesis](../../../terms/thesis.md) — a reason someone might disagree, an alternative explanation, or [evidence](./evidence.md) that cuts against the claim. A **concession** is the writer's acknowledgment that the counterargument has some validity.",
